Generic single-database configuration.

## Basic Alembic Commands

### Generate a new migration (auto-detecting changes)
```
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Description of changes"
```

### Apply all pending migrations
```
alembic upgrade head
```

### Downgrade to a previous version
```
alembic downgrade <revision>
```
or
```
alembic downgrade -1    # downgrade one revision
```

### View migration history
```
alembic history
```

### View current database revision
```
alembic current
```

### Create a new empty migration
```
alembic revision -m "Description of empty migration"
```

### Stamp the database with the current revision without running migrations
```
alembic stamp <revision>
```

### Show the SQL statements that would be executed for a migration
```
alembic upgrade <revision>:head --sql
```